@Rob Austein where wires might be getting crossed, is that (just like in rpki-rtr) - it is the  server's responsibility to merge/squeeze/aggregate (whatever we call it) the events into fewer deltas, and within a single delta is not allowed to ADD/REMOVE/ADD same object. 
But, the server can only buffer up & compress based on what the CA gave it to work with. If a RRDP server produces deltas every minute and CA is adding/removing ROAs every 5 minutes, the CA is going slower than the RRDP server can use to "bundle", and if the client is syncing every 15 minutes... you end up with 'full history replication' because there is no 'compression opportunity' (hope I am making myself clear)
In Rsync/Erik this behaviour is different than in RRDP because there is no shared session state between client and server
